MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1326472756}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 48fdfcc8a67199e4aa51c8e7b7b14715, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::WitcherRightVersion.Dialogue.DialogueInteractable
  displayName: Ghost of the Girl
  interactionPrompt: Listen
  startNodeId: start
  returnToElderNodeId: 
  completedQuestNodeId: 
  dialogueNodes:
  - Id: start
    SpeakerName: Ghost of the Girl
    Body: They gave me a witch's name after they killed me. The mirror learned it.
      The village learned it. Only the well kept the first sound.
    Choices:
    - Text: I found your medallion.
      NextNodeId: medallion
      FlagToSet: 
      QuestAction: ghost_memory_heard
      ClosesDialogue: 0
    - Text: Who killed you?
      NextNodeId: truth
      FlagToSet: 
      QuestAction: 
      ClosesDialogue: 0
    - Text: Fade back.
      NextNodeId: 
      FlagToSet: 
      QuestAction: 
      ClosesDialogue: 1
  - Id: truth
    SpeakerName: Ghost of the Girl
    Body: Not a monster. Not Elsa. Men with clean doorways and dirty hands. The elder
      sealed the order; Orten made mercy from forgetting.
    Choices:
    - Text: Then I need the seal and the diary.
      NextNodeId: 
      FlagToSet: 
      QuestAction: 
      ClosesDialogue: 1
  - Id: medallion
    SpeakerName: Ghost of the Girl
    Body: It remembers my pulse. Carry it to the final road, and the mirror will
      have to answer to the first version.
    Choices:
    - Text: I will carry the truth.
      NextNodeId: 
      FlagToSet: 
      QuestAction: 
      ClosesDialogue: 1
